<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by Shelter</title></head><body><div><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Shelter</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Shelter welcomes the opportunity to submit evidence to the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Work and Pensions</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Select Committee on the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> significant reforms</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> that have taken place in the welfare system over the past three years</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. More than </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">million people a year come to us for advice and support via our website, helpline </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and network of face-to-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">face services. Our evidence is rooted in the experiences of people we help every day, many of whom </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are extremely worried about housing costs and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">will be deeply affected by these changes. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">At a time when so many are struggling to make ends meet, losing a j</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ob or a serious illness is all it takes to tip people into a spiral that could end in homelessness.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Having access to a safety net can make all the difference</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> y</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">et the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">se reforms </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have cut the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> safety net back so much that if the worst happens families might n</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ot be able to get the help and support they need to stay in their homes and get back on their feet. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This submission </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">relates to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the most detrimental </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> related</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> welfare </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">reforms</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">restriction of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the Local Housing Allowance</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (LHA)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> rates means low income households are increasingly struggling to find af</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fordable private rented housing</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">removal of the 13 week protection</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> will</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> mean</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> m</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">any renters who lose their job</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> will </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">no longer have a grace period in which they can stay in their hom</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e while seeking a new job</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> proposals for the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">alternative to direct payments</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">for Universal Credit </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> insufficiently robust</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> react to rent arrears rather than proactively prevent them</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">so called</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> ‘b</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">edroom </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ax’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> takes little account of the legitimate needs of disabled people and others for additional space</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In addition, d</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ownsizing could</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> in fact</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> increase the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> bill, for example if affected households move into the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> more expensive</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> private rented sect</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">or</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Worryingly, the discretionary, short-term and cash-limited nature of Discretionary Housing Payments means they are inadequate to support people who have been hit by the reforms outlined in this submission and have no alternative support.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We therefore</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> make some practical recommendations to ensure these reforms work better, including:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The DWP commit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to review affordability and up-rate LHA rates if necessary to ensure low income households can access accommodation</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The ‘b</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">edroom </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ax’ should only apply </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">when alternative smaller accommodation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is unavailable</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and certain groups should be exempt</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The 13 week protection rule must be replicated under Universal Credit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Successive governments have moved to curb the rising cost of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> by adjusting benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> entitlement,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> but these efforts have focused on treating the symptoms rather than the cause.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> While this submission makes recommendations to mitigate against the worst effects of these welfare reforms, t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he Government must invest</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">buil</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ding new homes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> if it is serious about</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> bring</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> down the housing benefit bill</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. This is the only long term way to reduce the cost of housing and lift</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> households out of the benefit trap.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Local Housing Allowance Reforms </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">LHA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is a form of housing benefit paid to tenants in the private rented sector. Un</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">til April 2012, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">LHA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> rates were calculated on a monthly basis based on actual rents in a local market</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Benefit levels would stay the same or even fall if rental markets remained </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">steady</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, but if rents started rising due to market pressure, LHA rates would increase to ensure that low income private renting households could</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">find affordable accommodation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Welfare Reform Act broke this fundamental link between support for pr</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ivate re</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">nters and actual rents by linking </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">LHA rates to CPI inflation from April 2013. </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">his means LHA rates will fall behind the actual cost of private renting as private rents have traditionally risen faster than inflation (from 1997-2007 rents increased by </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">70 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">per cent but CPI only rose by</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">20 per cent</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">). </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Li</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">nking CPI to LHA would make a third of local authorities unaffordable to low income households by 2023</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Minister for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Welfare Reform acknowledged that</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> linking LHA to CPI </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">risks</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">creating a “critical lack of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> affordable housing”</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and said</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the Government was only committed to the measure until 2014-15</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, although the policy will automatically run on beyond the current spending review period</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. He pledged to reconsider LHA rates at this point if they </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">were </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">out of ste</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">p with local rents</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, with the option to increase rates</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Government must stick to this pledge. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">he </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Welfare Up-rating Act</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2013 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">implemented</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> a further cut, making it more likely that rents will outpace LHA.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">LHA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> rates will</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">be up-rated by</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a maximum of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">one </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">per cent</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in 2014-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">15 and 2015-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">16, even if rents or CPI are rising faster than this. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The least affordable areas will be exempt, but DWP has so far released insufficient evidence of how this will be calculated and distributed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> nor have they addressed concerns about the impact in other areas.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">he more LHA rates are held down, the greater the risk that low income households won’t be able to find affordable housing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> in the private rented sector</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This is exacerbated further by</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">an</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">dlords</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">aversi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">on</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to hous</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> tenants on benefi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ts. Successive reductions in h</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ousing </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">enefit </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> made claimants more unattractive to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">landlords</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><a href="http://england.shelter.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0005/570353/Interim_report_Sustain_private_rented_sector_research.pdf"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">A Big L</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">ottery funded project by Shelter and Crisis</span></a><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">showed </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">landlords’ unwillingness to accept tenants on LHA is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a major barrier to access</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> a private rented home</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In addition, separate </span><a href="http://england.shelter.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0008/659960/The_experiences_of_families_claiming_LHA_report_April_2013.pdf"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">e</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">vidence from Shelter</span></a><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> r</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">evealed how poorly the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">LHA </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">changes have</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> been communicated. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Claimants </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">we spoke to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> we</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">re </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">extremely confused about what</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> was changing and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">what it meant</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> for them. We found a t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">endency</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> for claimants</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to conflate different chan</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ges or to confuse</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> different</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> timetable</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">or example, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Universal Credit </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(UC) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> changes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> were referred to interchangeably</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. This </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">weaken</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> support for U</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">C and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> cause</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> unnecessary concern.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> The UC roll-out must seek to avoid replicating these communication errors. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">DWP </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">should </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">commit to a full </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">review of affordability in the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> sub-market</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">up-rate LHA rates if necessary</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> to ensure </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">low income households can access accommodation</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Social Secto</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">r </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Size C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">riteria</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">With the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">introduction</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">social </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">sector size</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">criteria</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (the so called ‘bedroom tax’)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in April 2013, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">660,000 people living in council or housing association homes had their </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> reduced as they had one or more rooms</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> judged to be “spare bedrooms”</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. Hard-pressed fami</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lies on the lowe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">st incomes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> now </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">need to find an average of £14 per week out of already stretched b</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">udgets to cover the shortfall. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Some will be unable to pay this shortfall and will </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cut back</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> on essential spending on food and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">household bills</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">O</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">thers may</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">tak</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> out debt, joining the one million households who used a pay day loan to cove</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">r their housing costs last year, while </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">many</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> may risk arrears, eviction and homelessness. This increases</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> costs for local authorities and undermines social housing as the last truly</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> affordable housing option for families on low incomes. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">f</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">households cannot</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> cover the difference there is not necessarily anywhere for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">them</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> to move</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> to, meaning they will be unable to escape the penalty</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. Because social landlords have tended to build homes to last families for many years, there is a lack of smaller one and two bed flats for households to downsize into. This is true nationally but </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a particular problem in certain areas.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">For example, i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">n S</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cotland we know</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> that</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of the 82,500 households affected by the social sector size criteria, 60,000 need to move to a 1 bedroom p</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">roperty to avoid the pe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nalty.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">urrently around 20,000 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">one</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> bedroom properties are let annual</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ly</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> across the whole of Scotland in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> social sector</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Downsizing could</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> actually</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> increase the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> bill, for example if affected households move into </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">more expensive alternatives such as </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">the private rented sector, a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">higher cost</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> social rent property (likely if transferring to newer acc</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ommodation or from council to housing association</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> accommodation) or into an A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ffordable </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">R</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ent </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">(up to 80% market rent) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">property. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Homeless households should not be penalised by the social sector size criteria.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">omeless households living in local authority owned temporary accommodation (TA) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">should be </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">exempt fro</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">m the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">under occupation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> penalty. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This is particularl</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">y a problem in Scotland where 56</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">% of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">TA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is local authority owned rather than leased or </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">licensed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> from a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">social or private landlord</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> where different subsidy rules apply. By definition, househ</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">olds who are forced to stay in TA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> unt</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">il a settled home is available </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are vulnerable and in stressful situation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and in particular need of a stable home to get back on their</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> feet.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The calculation of how many bedrooms a household needs is a crude assessment which takes little account of the legitimate needs of disabled people </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">and others </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">for additional space</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. Shelter has been approached by families who have good reasons for their ‘spare’ bedrooms, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">for example where</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> they need space to store essential medical equipment. Only very limited exemptions have been granted for disabled </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">children</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the DWP continues t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">o maintain that the over-stretched </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">DHP</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> fund is the best way to support disabled households.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> However,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> there is no guarantee that this will happen, and families have no right to appeal if DHP is not granted.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">n </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the case of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Burnip, Gorry and Trengrove</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the Court of Appeal ruled that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> regulations and not DHPs</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> should cater for disabled children who cannot share a bedroom due to different caring needs. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Where </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">DWP wish to support hard cases it would be more appropriate to do so via statuto</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ry regulations, which provide guaranteed protection, rather than unpredictable DHPs. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Even if DHPs were an appropriate tool to protect hard cases, the additional money that has been made available is unlikely to be sufficient. For example there is no guar</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">antee that the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">additional £25 million in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">intended to support disabled people living in homes with expensive adaptations</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> will be sufficient, and it is certain that many other disabled people will not be awarded a DHP</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">In England it has been calculated that the DHP budget </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">can </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">only</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> help one</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> in every 15 of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">all</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> households affected</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> by the bedroom tax</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> and in Scotland it is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">1 in 17 (6 per cent</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">), which means that a significant number of vulnerable people will not have access to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> a much-needed DHP payment.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The penalty </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">should </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">only appl</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">y</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> when alternative smaller accommodation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> is available and the tenant has</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> not made an attempt to downsize </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">There should be an exemption in regulations for:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">D</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">isabled people liv</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ing in</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> specially adapted homes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Households in local authority temporary accommodation </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">hose with legitimate reasons for needing the extra space including: </span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="circ