 be paid as a ‘Standard Payment’ for the majority of claimants</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> meaning claimants will receive a direct monthly payment to the household, inclusive </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Everyday money management is difficult for those on low i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ncomes and with complex needs. So, h</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">aving to m</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">anag</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> finances in this way </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">may therefore </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lead to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> arrears and ultimately eviction.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The DWP has announced </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">welcome </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">safeguards in the form of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Alternative Payments Arrangements (APAs)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> where </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the housing cost component of UC </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">will</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> be paid direct to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">landlord</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The APA proposals are welcome, but can be strengthened to ensure arrears are prevented in the first place.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The goal for UC claimants in settled accommodation should be improving financial capability to move those who can</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> to financial independence</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Each </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">claimant should be assessed to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">identify whether they should begin on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">tandard </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ayments or an APA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. The assessment </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">should </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">consider needs beyond money management and debt and cover financial literacy, access to appropriate financial products, and other circum</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">stances such as drug and alcohol addiction and debts. The assessment should result in a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> understanding of how long it might take the claimant to build financial capability and what support is required</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to make Standard Payments a realistic goal. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Households should have the option to self-refer for an assessment for APAs, at any time in their </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">UC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> application.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Importantly, APAs should be used to prevent arrears occurring in the first place.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Claimants who need A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">PAs </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">should be identified </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">up-front </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in collaboration with landlords, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Job Centre Plus, local authorities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and other</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> agencies to prevent them </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">moving into arrears</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> – the Local Delivery Partnerships charged with making </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">UC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> work on the ground would be a natural lead for this</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ll homeless </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">households i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">n </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">emporary </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ccommodation (TA) should</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> automat</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ically receive APAs </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">to ensure the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">housing </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">component of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">is paid to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">landlord until they move into settled accommodation. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">will ensure landlords receive rent and t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">hat people </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in TA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> who in the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> vast majority of cases have already been found homeless</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> do not get evicted and become homeless again.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">All claimants should be assessed for financial capability</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> at the start of their claim, and APAs </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">put in place for those who are not ready for Standard Payments </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">laimants who need APAs upfront </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">must be a priority;  Local Delivery Partnerships could lead on this </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Households should have the option to self-refer </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">for an assessment for A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">As </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">H</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ouseholds in TA </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">should </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">automatically receive APAs</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Universal Credit - 13 W</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">eek </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">rotection</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">In a little discussed move, short-term protection against rent arrears for people who have recently lost their job will be abolished under </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. Currently if someone </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has not claimed </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> in the previous 52 weeks and could afford their rent when they signed up to a tenancy, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">they can claim </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> for their full rent for 13 weeks. Under the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">UC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> this will be removed. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Housing benefit is subject to a num</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ber of regulations that limit the amount that can be paid out. This frequently means that people eligible for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> are not able to claim sufficient support to cover their actual rent.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> This is especially likely to affect private tenants as LHA ra</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">tes are purposely set below “average” rents. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">A comparison of median rents across Broad Rental Market Areas and LHA rates shows that a family renting a typical three bedroom home would have to make up more than £100 a month in over a quarter (27%) of loca</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">l authority areas in England if the 13 week protection rule is abolished. In more than two in five (43%) of local authorities families will have a shortfall of more than £75 a month.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he 13 week protection rule</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is intended to give people sufficient time t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">o find work and resume paying their rent independently or, if their circumstances are unlikely to improve, make a planned move into cheaper accommodation. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The majority of people </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">who lose their job </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">will only experience a short-term spell of unemployment. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Of the 325,000 unemployment claims that came to an end in June 2013, 53% of claimants were in receipt of JSA for 13 weeks or less</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. Shelter’s concern is that without an adequate safety net, people will be unable to bounce back and will be anxious about how</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> they will pay their housing costs at a time when they should be focused on getting bac</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">k into work. For some, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">inadequate support will tip them into arrears, eviction and homelessness. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The 13 week protection rule must be replicated under </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">, in a way that is compatible</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> with a unified benefit system</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The DWP </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">should </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">publish an impact assessment of the loss of the 13 week protection rule. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Discretionary Housing Payments</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Shelter is extremely concerned that Discretionary Housing Payments </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(DHPs) are being called upon inappropriately to support people with a predictable and clearly defined additional need, when statutory regulations would be better placed to avoid unintended consequences.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Concerns with DHPs:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">They are discretionary</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> - People cannot guarantee they will receive support, even if their circumstances are those that Ministers had in mind when releasing additional funding.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">They are short-term</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> –</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Although guidance does state that indefinite awards can be made if a claimant’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s circumstances are unlikely to change</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> local authorities are wary of doing this as it makes it harder to budget. Where a shortfall is ongoing and predictable people shouldn’t have to go through repeated applications.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">They are cash-limited</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> – The allocation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of DHP given to local councils is cash limited and insufficient to respond to everyone with a shortfall. The need to make the budget last throughout the year can also encourage local authorities not to publicise DHPs or to reject applications earlier in t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he year in case of a surge in demand later. Local authorities can top-up the DWP allocation by 1.5 times but are legally prohibited from spending anything beyond this. Moreover, many are unable to do so because of pressures on their budgets.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">n the firs</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t three months of 2013 th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ere was a sharp increase (of 60 per cent</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">) in the number of DHP applications </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in local authorities in England from </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">31,562</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (2011/12)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">50,393</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (2012/13)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. In 2011/12 the average number of DHP applications per local authority was 274, i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t rose to 420 in 2012/13, and just in the first three months of 2013/14 an average of 294 DHP applications have been received per local authority. We therefore do not expect the historic trend of local authorities returning unspent DHP allocations to be re</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">peated.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">R</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ecommend</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ations</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The DWP</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> should</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> introduce regulations to provide statutory protection for those hardest hit b</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">y the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">housing benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> changes</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The DHP budget must be distributed proportionately and transparently (according to need) across all the local authorities </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">in</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> the UK to target the most vulnerable people most effectively.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">26 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">September 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:9pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">6</span></p><p style="font-size:9pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="font-size:7pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt">13 week protection ensures that if someone has not claimed housing benefit in the previous 52 weeks and could afford their rent when they signed up to a tenancy, they can claim housing benefit for their full rent for 13 weeks if they lose their job. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">How will changes to Local Housing Allowance affect low-income tenants in private rented housing?</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt">Cambridge Centre for Housing and Planning Research, 2010)</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">The Impact of Welfare Reform Bill measures on affordability for low income private renting familie</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">s </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt">(Shelter, 2011)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt">HL Deb, 14 December 2011, c1324</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> Smith, M. Shelter and Crisis (June 2012) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Sustain: a longitudinal study of housing wellbeing in the private rented sector</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt">. Big Lottery Fund , </span><a href="http://england.shelter.org.uk/professional_resources/policy_and_practice/sustain"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt; text-decoration:underline">http://england.shelter.org.uk/professional_resources/policy_and_practice/sustain</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> Cass, N. GfK NOP on behalf of Shelter (April 2013)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">The experiences of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">families claiming housing benefits during a time of cuts and changes to benefits,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt; font-style:italic">Interim report</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:7pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7pt">Jobseeker’s Allowance claimant flows, June 2013.</span></p></body></html>